OL,3,CDrug-related deaths increase in
OL,4,CScotland and remain highest in Europe
OL,6,FBack in 2022, some 1,051 people died
OL,7,Fdue to drug misuse, which represented
OL,8,Fthe first significant drop in Scottish
OL,9,Fdrug deaths in a number of years.
OL,11,FNRS said after adjusting for age, the
OL,12,Frate of drug misuse deaths was 4.2
OL,13,Ftimes higher in 2023 than in 2000.
OL,15,FThe report also found that people in
OL,16,FScotland's most deprived areas were 15
OL,17,Ftimes more likely to die of drug
OL,18,Fmisuse last year than those in the
OL,19,Fleast deprived.
